#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:11
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading online"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:18
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&suse; offers an intuitive graphical and a simple command line tool to "
"upgrade a running system to a new service pack. They provide support for "
"<quote>rollback</quote> of service packs and more. This chapter explains how "
"to do a service pack upgrade step by step with these tools."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:27
#, no-c-format
msgid "Conceptual overview"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:29
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&suse; releases new service packs for the &sle; family at regular intervals. "
"To make it easy for customers to migrate to a new service pack and minimize "
"downtime, &suse; supports migrating online while the system is running."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:35
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Starting with &slea;&nbsp;12, &yast; Wagon has been replaced by &yast; "
"migration (GUI) and Zypper migration (command line). This has the following "
"advantages:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:43
#, no-c-format
msgid "The system is always in a defined state until the first RPM is updated."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:48
#, no-c-format
msgid "Canceling is possible until the first RPM is updated."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:53
#, no-c-format
msgid "Simple recovery, if there is an error."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:58
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is possible to do a <quote>rollback</quote> via system tools&mdash;no "
"backup or restore needed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:64
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use of all active repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:69
#, no-c-format
msgid "The ability to skip a service pack"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:76
#, no-c-format
msgid "Online migration not supported for major releases"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:77
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The online migration is <emphasis>only</emphasis> supported for migrating "
"between service packs. Online migration is <emphasis>not supported</"
"emphasis> for upgrading to new major releases. For details, see <xref "
"linkend=\"cha-upgrade-paths\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:83
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the offline migration to upgrade to a new major release. For details, "
"see <xref linkend=\"cha-upgrade-offline\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:90
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading &susemgr; clients"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:91
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the system to upgrade is a &susemgr; client, it cannot be upgraded by "
"&yast; online migration or <command>zypper migration</command> . Use the "
"<citetitle>Client Migration</citetitle> procedure instead. It is described "
"in the <link xlink:href=\"https://documentation.suse.com/suma/\"> "
"<citetitle>&susemgr; Upgrade Guide</citetitle></link> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:101
#, no-c-format
msgid "Service pack migration workflow"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:103
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A service pack migration can be executed by either &yast;, <command>zypper</"
"command> , or &ay;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:108
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before you can start a service pack migration, your system must be "
"registered at the &scc; or a local &rmt; server. &suse; Manager can also be "
"used."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:114
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Regardless of the method, a service pack migration consists of the following "
"steps:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:121
#, no-c-format
msgid "Find possible migration targets on your registered systems."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:126
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select one migration target."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:131
#, no-c-format
msgid "Request and enable new repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:136
#, no-c-format
msgid "Run the migration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:150
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The list of migration targets depends on the products you have installed and "
"registered. If you have an extension installed for which the new SP is not "
"yet available, it could be that no migration target is offered to you."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:156
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The list of migration targets available for your host will always be "
"retrieved from the &scc; and depend on products or extensions installed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:162
#, no-c-format
msgid "Canceling service pack migration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:164
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A service pack migration can only be canceled at specific stages during the "
"migration process:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:171
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Until the package upgrade starts, there are only minimal changes on the "
"system, like for services and repositories. Restore <filename>/etc/zypp/"
"repos.d/*</filename> to revert to the former state."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:178
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the package upgrade starts, you can revert to the former state by "
"using a Snapper snapshot (see <xref linkend=\"cha-snapper\"/> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:184
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the migration target was selected, &scc; changes the repository data. "
"To revert this state manually, use <command>SUSEConnect</command> <option>--"
"rollback</option> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:193
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading with the online migration tool (&yast;)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:195
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To perform a service pack migration with &yast;, use the <guimenu>Online "
"Migration</guimenu> tool. By default, &yast; does not install any packages "
"from a third-party repository. If a package was installed from a third-party "
"repository, &yast; prevents packages from being replaced with the same "
"package coming from &suse;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:211
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Deactivate all unused extensions on your registration server to avoid future "
"dependency conflicts. If you forget an extension, &yast; will later detect "
"unused extension repositories and deactivate them."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:241
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Run &yast; online update to get the latest package updates for your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:247
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Install the package <package>yast2-migration</package> and its dependencies "
"(in &yast; under <menuchoice> <guimenu>Software</guimenu> <guimenu>Software "
"Management</guimenu> </menuchoice> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:256
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Restart &yast;, otherwise the newly installed module will not be shown in "
"the control center."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:262
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &yast;, choose <guimenu>Online Migration</guimenu> (depending on the "
"version of &productname; that you are upgrading from, this module is "
"categorized under either <guimenu>System</guimenu> or <guimenu>Software</"
"guimenu> ). &yast; will show possible migration targets and a summary. If "
"more than one migration target is available for your system, select one from "
"the list."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:272
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select one migration target from the list and proceed with <guimenu>Next</"
"guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:278
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case the migration tool offers update repositories, it is recommended to "
"proceed with <guimenu>Yes</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:284
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<remark>toms 2015-09-09: FATE#319140</remark> If the Online Migration tool "
"finds obsolete repositories coming from DVD or a local server, it is highly "
"recommended to disable them. Obsolete repositories are from a previous SP. "
"Any old repositories from &scc; or &rmt; are removed automatically."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:293
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Check the summary and proceed with the migration by clicking <guimenu>Next</"
"guimenu> . Confirm with <guimenu>Start Update</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:300
#, no-c-format
msgid "After the successful migration restart your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:307
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading with Zypper"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:309
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To perform a service pack migration with Zypper, use the command line tool "
"<command>zypper</command> <option>migration</option> from the package "
"<package>zypper-migration-plugin</package> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:317
#, no-c-format
msgid "To start the service pack migration, do the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:323
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are logged in to a GNOME session running on the machine you are going "
"to update, switch to a text console. Running the update from within a GNOME "
"session is not recommended. Note that this does not apply when being logged "
"in from a remote machine (unless you are running a VNC session with GNOME)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:332
#, no-c-format
msgid "Register your &sle; machine if you have not done so:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:335
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;<command>SUSEConnect</command> --regcode "
"<replaceable>YOUR_REGISTRATION_CODE</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:352
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start the migration:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:355
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;<command>zypper migration</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:356
#, no-c-format
msgid "Some notes about the migration process:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:361
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If more than one migration target is available for your system, Zypper "
"allows you to select one SP from the list. This is the same as skipping one "
"or more SPs. Keep in mind, online migration for base products (&slsa;, "
"&sleda;) remains available only between the SPs of a major version."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:370
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default, Zypper uses the option <option>--no-allow-vendor-change</option> "
"which is passed to <command>zypper</command> <option>dup</option> . If a "
"package was installed from a third-party repository, this option prevents "
"packages from being replaced with the same package coming from &suse;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:379
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<remark>toms 2015-09-09: FATE#319140</remark> If Zypper finds obsolete "
"repositories coming from DVD or a local server, it is highly recommended to "
"disable them. Old &scc; or &rmt; repositories are removed automatically."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:389
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Review all the changes, especially the packages that are going to be "
"removed. Proceed by typing <literal>y</literal> (the exact number of "
"packages to upgrade can vary on your system):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:394
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"266 packages to upgrade, 54 to downgrade, 17 new, 8 to reinstall, 5 to "
"remove, 1 to change arch.\n"
"Overall download size: 285.1 MiB. Already cached: 0 B  After the operation, "
"additional 139.8 MiB will be used.\n"
"Continue? [y/n/? shows all options] (y):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:397
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the <keycombo> <keycap function=\"shift\"/> <keycap function=\"pageup\"/"
"> </keycombo> or <keycombo> <keycap function=\"shift\"/> <keycap function="
"\"pagedown\"/> </keycombo> keys to scroll in your shell."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:404
#, no-c-format
msgid "After successful migration restart your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:411
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading with plain Zypper"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:413
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If your system is not registered because you do not have access to the "
"Internet or a registration server, migrating to a new service pack is not "
"possible with &yast; Migration or <command>zypper migration</command> . In "
"this case you can still migrate to a new service pack with plain Zypper and "
"some manual interactions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:422
#, no-c-format
msgid "For unregistered systems only"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:423
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This migration path to a new service pack is <emphasis>only</emphasis> "
"supported for unregistered systems that do not have access to the Internet "
"or a registration server. This may, for example, be the case for machines in "
"a specially protected network. If you have a registered system, use &yast; "
"or Zypper migration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:433
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installation sources"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:434
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This migration path requires you to provide the installation sources for the "
"new service pack in a place that can be accessed by the machine you are "
"going to migrate. This can for example be achieved by setting up an &rmt; "
"server or an SLP server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:440
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is also required that the system has access to an up-to-date update "
"repository for the installed product version."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:448
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are logged in to a graphical session running on the machine you are "
"going to migrate, log out of that session and switch to a text console. "
"Running the update from within a graphical session is not recommended. Note "
"that this does not apply when being logged in from a remote machine (unless "
"you are running a VNC session with X)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:457
#, no-c-format
msgid "Update the package management tools with the old &sle; repositories:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:460
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;<command>zypper</command> patch --updatestack-only"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:463
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Get a list of packages that currently do not have a repository assigned to "
"them (orphaned packages). These packages will not be migrated and there is "
"no guarantee that they will work after the migration (because other packages "
"they rely on may have changed in such a way that they are no longer "
"compatible). To get the list, run:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:471
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Carefully review the list and remove all orphaned packages that are no "
"longer needed. Make a note of all remaining orphaned packages, you will need "
"it later for comparison."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:478
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Get a list of all repositories that the system is currently subscribed to by "
"running:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:482
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper repos -u"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:483
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Update each repository URL so that its product version number is "
"<literal>&product-ga;-SP&product-sp;</literal> . For example, if the URL of "
"a repository is"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:488
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"http://rmt.&exampledomain;/repo/SUSE/Products/SLE-15-SP1-Product-SLES/x86_64/"
"product/"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:489
#, no-c-format
msgid "change it to"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:492
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"http://rmt.&exampledomain;/repo/SUSE/Products/SLE-15-SP2-Product-SLES/x86_64/"
"product/"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:493
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This needs to be done with all repositories that are enabled. You may want "
"to consider also doing this for repositories that are currently disabled, to "
"avoid having wrong installation sources in the system when activating them "
"at a later point in time."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:499
#, no-c-format
msgid "To change the repository URLs you have the following options:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:504
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using <menuchoice> <guimenu>&yast;</guimenu> <guimenu>Software</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>Software Repositories</guimenu></menuchoice> . Select a repository "
"and click <guimenu>Edit</guimenu> to make the required change. Repeat this "
"for all repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:512
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using Zypper. Remove the old repository by running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:515
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper removerepo <replaceable>OLD_REPO_ID</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:516
#, no-c-format
msgid "Then add the corresponding new repository by running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:519
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;zypper addrepo -f <replaceable>URL</replaceable> "
"<replaceable>NAME</replaceable>-&product-ga;-SP&product-sp;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:522
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By editing repository configuration files in <filename>/etc/zypp/repos.d</"
"filename> . Each repository is represented by one configuration file. "
"Changing the value for the <literal>baseurl</literal> parameter is required "
"in each file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:532
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Review your changes by running <command>zypper repos -u</command> and update "
"the repositories by running:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:537
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case updating a repository fails, double-check whether you entered the "
"wrong URL. If the problem cannot be fixed, it is recommended to disable the "
"failing repository."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:542
#, no-c-format
msgid "If all repositories are correctly configured, run"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:545
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper refresh -f -s"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:546
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"again, to make sure <emphasis>all</emphasis> repositories are up-to-date."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:551
#, no-c-format
msgid "Before starting the migration it is recommended do a test run first:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:554
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper dup -D --no-allow-vendor-change --no-recommends"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:555
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The parameter <option>-D</option> will perform a dry-run that simulates the "
"migration without actually changing the system. If problems occur, fix them "
"before proceeding. In case the test run succeeds, perform the real migration "
"by running:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:561
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper dup --no-allow-vendor-change --no-recommends"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:562
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<option>-no-allow-vendor-change</option> ensures that third-party RPMs will "
"not overwrite RPMs from the base system. The option <option>--no-recommends</"
"option> ensures that packages deselected during initial installation will "
"not be added again."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:570
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When the migration has finished and the system has booted into the new "
"service pack version, run the check for orphaned packages again:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:574
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper packages --orphaned"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:575
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Compare the new list with the one you generated before starting the "
"migration. If new packages appear in the list, it may be because they were "
"moved to a different module in the new service pack. If you did not have "
"that module in the previous installation, the package did not get updated."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:581
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can check to which module a package belongs at <link xlink:href="
"\"https://scc.suse.com/packages\"/> . Add the missing modules using "
"<command>zypper addrepo</command> or the &yast; Software Repositories "
"module, and update the orphaned packages afterwards by running:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:588
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;zypper install --no-recommends <replaceable>LIST OF PACKAGES</"
"replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:591
#, no-c-format
msgid "You have successfully migrated to a new service pack!"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:599
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rolling back a service pack"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:601
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a service pack does not work for you, &sle; supports reverting the system "
"to the state before the service pack migration was started. Prerequisite is "
"a Btrfs root partition with snapshots enabled (this has been the default "
"since &slsa;&nbsp;12). See <xref linkend=\"cha-snapper\"/> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:609
#, no-c-format
msgid "Get a list of all Snapper snapshots:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:612
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;snapper list"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:613
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Review the output to locate the snapshot that was created immediately before "
"the service pack migration was started. The column <guimenu>Description</"
"guimenu> contains a corresponding statement and the snapshot is marked as "
"<literal>important</literal> in the column <guimenu>Userdata</guimenu> . "
"Memorize the snapshot number from the column <guimenu>#</guimenu> and its "
"date from the column <guimenu>Date</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:624
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Reboot the system. From the boot menu, select <guimenu>Start boot loader "
"from a read-only snapshot</guimenu> and then choose the snapshot with the "
"date and number you memorized in the previous step. A second boot menu (the "
"one from the snapshot) is loaded. Select the entry starting with &slsa;&nbsp;"
"&productnumber; and boot it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:633
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The system boots into the previous state with the system partition mounted "
"read-only. Log in as &rootuser; and check whether you have chosen the "
"correct snapshot. Also make sure everything works as expected. Note that "
"since the root file system is mounted read-only, restrictions in "
"functionality may apply."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:640
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case of problems or if you have booted the wrong snapshot, reboot and "
"choose a different snapshot to boot from&mdash;up to this point no permanent "
"changes have been made. If the snapshot is correct and works as expected, "
"make the change permanent by running the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:646
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;snapper rollback"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:647
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Reboot afterward. On the boot screen, choose the default boot entry to "
"reboot into the reinstated system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:653
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Check if the repository configuration has been properly reset. Furthermore, "
"check if all products are properly registered. If either one is not the "
"case, updating the system at a later point in time may no longer work, or "
"the system may be updated using the wrong package repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:660
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure the system can access the Internet before starting this procedure."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:666
#, no-c-format
msgid "Refresh services and repositories by running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:669
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper ref -fs"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:672
#, no-c-format
msgid "Get a list of active repositories by running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:675
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper lr"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:676
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Carefully check the output of this command. No services and repositories "
"that were added for the update should be listed. For example, if you are "
"rolling back from &slsa;&nbsp;&productnumber; to &slsa;&product-ga; GA, the "
"list must contain the <literal>SLES&product-ga;-GA</literal> repositories, "
"and not the <literal>SLES&product-ga;-SP&product-sp;</literal> repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:684
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If wrong repositories are listed, delete them and, if necessary, replace "
"them with the versions matching your product or service pack version. For a "
"list of repositories for the supported migration paths refer to <xref "
"linkend=\"sec-upgrade-background-modules\"/> . (Note that manual "
"intervention should not be necessary, as the repositories should be updated "
"automatically, but it is a best practice to verify and make any necessary "
"corrections.)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:695
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Last, check the registration status for all products installed by running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:699
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;SUSEConnect --status"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:700
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All products should be reported as being <literal>Registered</literal> . If "
"this is not the case, repair the registration by running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:705
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;SUSEConnect --rollback"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:710
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you have successfully reverted the system to the state that was captured "
"immediately before the service pack migration was started."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:717
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading with &susemgr;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:719
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&susemgr; is a server solution for providing updates, patches, and security "
"fixes for &sle; clients. It comes with a set of tools and a Web-based user "
"interface for management tasks. See <link xlink:href=\"https://www.suse.com/"
"products/suse-manager/\"/> for more information about &susemgr;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:727
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"SP Migration allows migrating from one Service Pack (SP) to another within "
"one major version (for example, from &slsa;&nbsp;&product-ga;&nbsp;GA to "
"&slsa;&nbsp;&product-ga;&nbsp;SP&product-sp;)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:737
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading from &opensuse; Leap to &productname;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:738
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can upgrade an &opensuse; Leap installation to &productname;. The "
"procedure is similar to <xref linkend=\"sec-upgrade-online-yast\"/> , but "
"requires some additional steps. Before executing this procedure on a "
"production system, we recommend to first run it on a test system that "
"replicates your production setup."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:745
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To find out which &opensuse; Leap versions are supported for migration, "
"refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-upgrade-paths-supported\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:754
#, no-c-format
msgid "Not all &opensuse; packages can be migrated"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:755
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&opensuse; provides more packages than &productname;. Most of the additional "
"packages are available through &ph; and will be migrated. Any additional "
"packages that are not available through &ph; will no longer receive updates "
"after the migration and should therefore be removed afterward."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:761
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure that all packages you need for operating your system are available "
"in the &productname; and &ph; repositories. For more information about &ph;, "
"refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-add-ons-package-hub\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:768
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading &opensuse; Leap to &productname;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:769
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To migrate from &opensuse; Leap to &productname;, execute the following "
"steps:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:774
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Switch to a TTY, for example by pressing <keycombo><keycap function=\"control"
"\"/> <keycap function=\"alt\"/><keycap>F1</keycap></keycombo> . Then log in "
"as &rootuser;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:781
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Install the <package>yast2-registration</package> and <package>rollback-"
"helper</package> packages:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:785
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;<command>zypper in yast2-registration rollback-helper</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:796
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enable the <systemitem class=\"service\">rollback-helper</systemitem> "
"service:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:800
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>systemctl enable rollback</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:803
#, no-c-format
msgid "Register the system with the &scc;:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:806
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>yast2 registration</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:809
#, no-c-format
msgid "Perform the migration:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:812
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>yast2 migration</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:813
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case of package conflicts, &yast; presents a list of resolutions to "
"choose from."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:819
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remove orphaned packages:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:822
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;<command>zypper rm $(zypper --no-refresh packages --orphaned | "
"gawk '{print $5}' | tail -n +5)</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:825
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reboot the system:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:828
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>reboot</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:831
#, no-c-format
msgid "You have now successfully migrated your system to &productname;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:834
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you run into a problem after the migration, you can revert the migration "
"like a service pack upgrade. For instructions, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-"
"upgrade-online-rollback\"/> ."
msgstr ""
